/main method
JnS subInputNames
JnS subPrintString
JnS subChangeCase
Load threehundred
Store printNameAdd
JnS subPrintString
Halt


/subroutine for inputting names
subInputNames,HEX 0
/loop so that it goes on until the user inputs a $
Loop,		  Input
              StoreI myNameAdd
			  Subt dollarsign
              Skipcond 400
              Jump iscommainput
			  JumpI subInputNames
                            
AddnextLine,  Load myNameAdd
			  Add one
              Store myNameAdd
              Load count
			  Subt one
              Store count
              Skipcond 800
              Jump Addcommasorfullstop
			  Jump Loop

/This is to check whether the user inputted a comma or not
iscommainput, LoadI myNameAdd
			  Subt comma
              Skipcond 400
              Jump isfullstopinput
              Jump commainput

/This is to add comma and store a temporary variable so that I can
/store in the right address
commainput,	Load count
            Store Tempcomma
            Load five
            Store count
            Load myNameAdd
			Add one
            Store myNameAdd
            Load commaornot
			Add one
            Store commaornot
            Jump Loop

/This is to check whether the user inputted a full stop or not
isfullstopinput, LoadI myNameAdd
                 Subt fullstop
                 Skipcond 400
                 Jump AddnextLine
                 Jump AddingmyNameAdd
               
/This code right here is so that the next name can be stored at the right address
/if the input is less than 5 characters. Also resets the count to be used
/in the next loop
AddingmyNameAdd, Load count
           		 Store Tempfullstop
		   		 Load myNameAdd
		   		 Add Tempcomma
		         Store myNameAdd
		         Add Tempfullstop
                 Store myNameAdd
                 Load five
                 Store count
                 Load myNameAdd
                 Add five
                 Store myNameAdd
                 Load zero
				 Store Tempcomma
				 Load zero
                 Store Tempfullstop
                 Load commaornot
 				 Subt one
                 Store commaornot
                 Jump Loop

/This is to check whether we need to add a comma or a full stop              
Addcommasorfullstop, Load commaornot
					 Skipcond 400
                     Jump Addfullstop
					 Jump Addcomma

/This is the code to add a comma
Addcomma, Load comma
	      StoreI myNameAdd
          Load myNameAdd
          Add one
          Store myNameAdd
          Load commaornot
          Add one
          Store commaornot
          Load count
          Add five
          Store count
          Jump Loop

/This is the code to add a fullstop
Addfullstop, Load fullstop
 			 StoreI myNameAdd
             Load myNameAdd
             Add five
             Store myNameAdd
             Add Tempcomma
			 Store myNameAdd
             Load commaornot
             Subt one
             Store commaornot
             Load count
             Add five
             Store count
             Load zero
             Store Tempcomma
             Jump Loop

/this subroutine is for printing the strings out
subPrintString, Hex 0
/this is the loop for printing as well as checking if the value stored is a comma or not
/ if it is then we print out the space character
Loopprint,	LoadI printNameAdd
			Subt comma
			Skipcond 400
            Jump isfullstopprint
            Load space
            Output
			Load printNameAdd
			Add one
            Store printNameAdd
			Jump Loopprint

/This is to check whether the value in the memory is a full stop or not
/ and if it is then it will print out a new line
isfullstopprint, LoadI printNameAdd
				 Subt fullstop
				 Skipcond 400
                 Jump isdollar
                 Load newline
				 Output
                 Load printNameAdd
				 Add one
                 Store printNameAdd
				 Jump Loopprint


/This is to check whether the value in the memory is a dollar sign or not and if it is
/then we jump out of the subroutine
isdollar, LoadI printNameAdd
		  Subt dollarsign
		  Skipcond 400
          Jump is0
		  JumpI subPrintString

/This is to check whether the value in the memory is a 0000 or not and if it is,
/then we just ignore it and it will just continue on into the loop
is0, LoadI printNameAdd
	 Skipcond 400
     Jump Print
     Load printNameAdd
	 Add one
     Store printNameAdd
	 Jump Loopprint

/This is to print the output of alphabet characters
Print, LoadI printNameAdd
	   Output
       Load printNameAdd
	   Add one
       Store printNameAdd
       Jump Loopprint

/subroutine for changing capital to lower case or lower case to capital
subChangeCase, Hex 0
/This is the loop for changing the cases and to check whether the value stored is 
/a comma or not
Loopchange, LoadI changeCaseName
			Subt comma
            Skipcond 400
            Jump isfullstopchange
			Load changeCaseName
			Add one
            Store changeCaseName
            Jump Loopchange

/This is to check whether the value is a full stop or not
isfullstopchange, LoadI changeCaseName
				  Subt fullstop
                  Skipcond 400
                  Jump isdollarchange
                  Load changeCaseName
				  Add one
                  Store changeCaseName
				  Jump Loopchange
                  
/This is to check whether the value is a dollar sign or not
isdollarchange, LoadI changeCaseName
				Subt dollarsign
				Skipcond 400
                Jump is0change
                JumpI subChangeCase

/This is to check whether the value is a 0000 or not
is0change, LoadI changeCaseName
		   Skipcond 400
           Jump changeNameLowerCase
           Load changeCaseName
		   Add one
           Store changeCaseName
		   Jump Loopchange

/This is to check whether the value stored is a capital letter or not and if it is not
/then we change it into a capital letter
changeNameLowerCase, LoadI changeCaseName
					 Subt ninety
                     Skipcond 800
                     Jump changeNameCapital
                     LoadI changeCaseName
					 Subt thirtytwo
					 StoreI changeCaseName
					 Load changeCaseName
					 Add one
            		 Store changeCaseName
					 Jump Loopchange

/This is to change the letter from capital letter to lower case
changeNameCapital, LoadI changeCaseName
				   Add thirtytwo
				   StoreI changeCaseName
				   Load changeCaseName
				   Add one
                   Store changeCaseName
				   Jump Loopchange


myNameAdd, Hex 300
printNameAdd, Hex 300
commaornot, Dec 0
count, DEC 5
zero, DEC 0
one, DEC 1
five, DEC 5
comma, DEC 44
fullstop, DEC 46
dollarsign, DEC 36
Tempcomma, Dec 0
Tempfullstop, Dec 0
space, Dec 32
newline, Dec 10
changeCaseName, Hex 300
thirtytwo, Dec 32
threehundred, Hex 300
ninety, Dec 90